'''應急可轉債'''（英語：'''Contingent Convertible Bond （CoCo）'''，也稱作'''Enhanced Capital Note （ECN）'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fixedincomeinvestments.org.uk/fixed-income-terms-explained-1/what-are-ecns |title=Fixed Income Investments |access-date=2016-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131195607/http://www.fixedincomeinvestments.org.uk/fixed-income-terms-explained-1/what-are-ecns |archive-date=2016-01-31 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>），俗稱CoCo債，是一種[[固定收益|固定收益]]產品。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fixedincomeinvestments.org.uk/fixed-income-terms-explained-1/what-are-ecns |title=Fixed Income Investments |access-date=2016-02-16 |archive-date=2016-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131195607/http://www.fixedincomeinvestments.org.uk/fixed-income-terms-explained-1/what-are-ecns |dead-url=yes }}</ref>如果某個事件被觸發，如银行资本充足率不足，或股价低于某一价格，或财务指标低于监管层要求时，发行方有权单方面停付利息或强制把债券转换为[[股權|股權]]。此類債券可以采取各种不同的形式，如作為銀行備用的後償貸款融通、大災害債券、或一个增强型反向转换的看涨期權。<ref>{{harvp|Pazarbasioglu|Zhou|Lesle|Moore|2011|p=4}}</ref>。應急可轉債这个概念是[[罗伯特·科克斯·默顿|罗伯特·科克斯·默顿]]教授在1990年提出，<ref>{{Cite journal|title = The Financial System and Economic Performance|journal = Journal of Financial Services Research|date = 1990-12-04|url = http://robertcmerton.com/publication/the-financial-system-and-economic-performance/|access-date = 2021-01-26|archive-date = 2020-09-22|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200922074848/https://robertcmerton.com/publication/the-financial-system-and-economic-performance/|dead-url = no}}</ref>並於1991年《[[哈佛法律评论|哈佛法律评论]]》上发表。<ref>{{Cite journal|title = Distress-Contingent Convertible Bonds: A Proposed Solution to the Excess Debt Problem|jstor = 1341621|journal = Harvard Law Review|date = 1991-01-01|pages = 1857–1877|volume = 104|issue = 8|doi = 10.2307/1341621}}</ref>  

